{
  "stem": "2916.5",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Now, the liberation was a horrible affair because the army, the Americans, were still fighting.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were not ready to treat--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were actually liberated on April 30, 1945.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We stayed in Seeshaupt for another week, during which the war ended.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And many, many of the injured died because there was no medical treatment.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Again, I-- in order to go into detail would take too long.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I understand that the young American soldiers were fighting a war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They didn't expect what they saw.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they did not-- were not certainly prepared for treating sick people or injured or give us food.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So it was up to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And some Germans set up sort of cauldrons on the street, and they cooked potatoes, and they gave us food.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But many people continued dying after liberation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "From here, we were taken to a large military camp in Munich called Flakkaserne where we were about a month.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And from here, people who were-- who, who decided not to return to their homes were then again shipped to other camps, refugee camps that were called DP camps, displaced persons camp.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Those who decided to go back to their homes, which was called repatriation-- you had to sign up.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My mother, my brother, and I-- we signed up for repatriation and we were put on-- because we wanted to go home and see who else returned.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were sure my father survived because he was still young and athletic.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so we were-- we were put on trucks, American vehicles, and driven to Czechoslovakia one month after Seeshaupt.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And at that time, they weighed us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I was already 53 kilo, and my brother was still only 45 kilo.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he was a very-- he's a very tall man.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
